Context:
SearchResults.tsx line 69 filters installed plugins:
```tsx
const installedMatches = filterLower ? plugins.filter(p => matchesPlugin(p, filterLower)) : plugins;
```

`matchesPlugin` from bridge.ts matches against plugin name, displayName, and all tool names/descriptions.

The e2e-test plugin has tools like 'echo', 'greet', 'list_items'. Typing 'echo' should show only the e2e-test plugin card.

The 'Installed' section header (line 96): `<SectionHeader>Installed</SectionHeader>`

Test approach:
```typescript
const sidePanel = await openSidePanel(context);
// Wait for plugins to load
await expect(sidePanel.getByText('E2E Test')).toBeVisible({ timeout: 15_000 });

// Type 'echo' in search
await sidePanel.getByPlaceholder('Search plugins and tools...').fill('echo');

// Installed section header should appear
await expect(sidePanel.getByText('Installed')).toBeVisible();

// e2e-test plugin should be visible
await expect(sidePanel.getByText('E2E Test')).toBeVisible();

// Clear search
await sidePanel.getByPlaceholder('Search plugins and tools...').fill('');

// All plugins visible again, no Installed header
await expect(sidePanel.getByText('Installed')).toBeHidden();
```

