Context:
SearchResults.tsx lines 88-89:
```tsx
const showNoResults =
  toolFilter && !hasInstalledResults && !npmSearching && !npmSearchError && availableResults.length === 0;
```
Line 152:
```tsx
{showNoResults && <div className="py-8 text-center text-muted-foreground text-sm">No results</div>}
```

The 'No results' only shows when:
1. There's a search query (`toolFilter` truthy)
2. No installed plugins match
3. npm search is done (`!npmSearching`)
4. npm search didn't error (`!npmSearchError`)
5. No npm results match

Search for 'xyzzy99nonexistent' — no installed plugin matches, and npm registry returns empty.

```typescript
await sidePanel.getByPlaceholder('Search plugins and tools...').fill('xyzzy99nonexistent');
// Wait for npm search to complete (loading spinner appears then disappears)
// Then verify 'No results'
await expect(sidePanel.getByText('No results')).toBeVisible({ timeout: 15_000 });
await expect(sidePanel.getByText('Installed')).toBeHidden();
await expect(sidePanel.getByText('Available')).toBeHidden();
```

Mark test.slow() since it waits for the real npm search to return empty.

